quote.p:
—We believe that domestic political concerns would argue in favor of testing;
                        and that these concerns weigh more heavily than foreign policy
                        considerations in a decision whether or not to test;

div.p:
23. The relevant question, we believe, is not, “why would they test quickly?”;
                    but rather, under what condition or circumstances would they be induced to delay
                    a test shot?

quote.p:
—We do not foresee any circumstances which would induce South Africa to
                        terminate, or even to postpone for a prolonged or indefinite period, its
                        nuclear weapons program;
